<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-758-888  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 758 888.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 9 1989 v6 n40 p29(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Digi-Data adds SCSI interface to VHS-based backup systems.andO;(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted SMalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digi-Data Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Digi-data Gigastore SC (Computer apparatus) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSmall Computer Systems InterfaceBack-Up Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Digi-Data Adds SCSI Interface To VHS-Based Backup SystemsandM;JESSUP, Md.andP;  -- In an effort to drum up business in the workstation market,Digi-Data has added a SCSI interface to its line of backup subsystems thatare based on VHS tape.andM;Gigastore 2.5 SC, Gigastore 3.7 SC and Gigastore 5.4 SC include a SCSIinterface with a maximum data transfer rate of 4MHz per second.andM;In contrast to 8mm drives, the Gigastore, 5.4 SC drive boasts a slightlyhigher maximum bit transfer rate of 250KB per second, as opposed to the246KB-per-second transfer rate offered by 8mm tape, company officials said.andM;The subsystem's 5.4GB storage capacity also exceeds the 2.3GB of storageavailable on 8mm drives, the officials added.andM;The helical scan VCR videotape drives have dual buffers of 512KB,three-minute average search times and error rates of approximately one bi'per 10 bits.andM;Gigastore 2.5 SC and Gigastore 3.7 SC have sustainable data transfer rates of120KB per second.andP;  Gigastore 5.4 SC has a rate of 250KB per second, accordingto Digi-Data officials.andM;The three new drives are now available.andP;  Gigastone 2.5 SC is $3,600;Gigastore 3.7 SC is $4,900; and Gigastore 5.4 is $6,900.andM;Digi-Data Corp. is located at 8580 Dorsey Run Road, Jessup, MD 20794, (301)498-0200.andO;</TEXT></DOC>